> At the Fresh Farm, we've noticed that the word 'Cajun' is thrown around a lot! It's
> always 'Cajun this' and 'Cajun that'. But Cajun isn't just another spice like paprika
> or cumin, it's a whole cooking tradition created by the French when they moved
> to Southern Louisiana. It was born out of fusion! So we're taking our beloved
> friend fusion a bit further, by adding the sweet, hot flavours of Cajun spices
> to some delicious lemony British cod. Enjoy!

Put the @Cod Fillets{2} in a #bowl{} along with the @Lemon{1/2}(juiced), the
@Cajun Spice Mix{1.5} (if you don't like things too spicy, only add half the Cajun
spice mix), a @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{a good grind}. Gently
combine so your fish gets a good coating of the spice.

Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Chop the @Potato{1} into roughly 2cm pieces.
Peel and chop the top and bottom off the @Carrot{2}, chop lengthways into slices
about 2cm wide, then chop these into batons about the size of your index finger.
Pull the leaves off the @Thyme{5}(leaves pulled).

Pop your potato and carrot on a #baking tray{}, drizzle over a splash of @oil{a splash},
your thyme leaves, a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{a good grind}
and give it a shake so everything gets a good coating. Cook in your oven for
~{30%minutes} until your potatoes are crispy and your carrots tender.

Chop the @Courgette{1} into similar sized batons as the carrot. Peel and finely
chop the @Garlic Clove{2}(finely chopped). When your potato and carrot have been
cooking for ~{15%minutes} add your courgette to the #baking tray{} as well and cook
for the last ~{15%minutes}.

When your vegetables are 10 mins from being cooked, put the @Neptune Butter Salted{1.5}
in a #nonstick frying pan{} on medium-low heat. Once hot, add your garlic and cook
for ~{1%minute}, before adding your fish skin-side down. Tip: Don't put all your
lemony spice mix in the pan yet, save it for later. Cook for ~{3%minutes} on one
side before turning your fish over and cooking for ~{2-3%minutes} on the other side.
Tip: The fish is ready when it turns from clear to opaque throughout, careful not
to burn! Remove from the pan. Add your remaining lemony spice mix to the pan along
with a splash of @water{splash}, and warm through for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Get your veggies out of your oven. Serve your fish on top of your veggies and drizzle
the buttery lemon juices from your pan over the top. Voilà!